external_knowledge:
- 'Highlight' or 'dawn' metaphorically refers to the status dates '2020-02-10' and '2020-01-30';
- The 'glimpses caught' of their genetic voyage refer to the sequencing results;
- The 'beacon of light' metaphorically refers to the hospital name;
- The 'phase of their expedition' refers to the status of the case.

- "Close contact of imported case" refers to cases where an individual has been in close proximity to a person who has entered the country and is confirmed to be infected;
- "Wuhan, China" is a reference to the city in Hubei province where the initial outbreak of a certain communicable disease occurred;
- "Hong Kong" is the transmission location, indicating where the disease spread from the imported case to another person.

'hospitalized' is metaphorically referred to as 'navigating the stormy seas of recovery';
'order by age DESC' means sorting the oldest first;
'order by nationality ASC' means sorting nationalities alphabetically;
'top 10 records' means selecting the first 10 entries.

sql:
SELECT sequencing_result 
FROM case_sequencing 
WHERE sequencing_date = '2020-02-01';

SELECT case_id, contact_name, contact_phone, contact_email, contact_address
FROM case_contacts
WHERE case_id = 0;

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM case_exposure
WHERE exposure_type = 'Close contact';

SELECT exposure_history, COUNT(*) AS NumberOfCases
FROM cases
GROUP BY exposure_history;
